{
  "texts": [
    "For practical guidance on implementing the SAFE procedure, we have included a comprehensive 'cheat sheet' [see Additional file 1].",
    "This adaptable resource provides a framework for researchers to input their chosen machine learning models and parameters, along with stopping heuristics, tailored to the specific needs of their review.",
    "Note that we provide some values, like percentages or the number of records; these numbers should be merely used as an example and are in no way meant as exact rules.",
    "Similarly, the machine learning models referenced here serve as examples; researchers should feel encouraged to select or adapt models that best suit their specific requirements and preferences.",
    "Phase 1: screen a random set of training dataIn order to train the first iteration of the machine learning model, it is necessary to have training data available consisting of at least one labeled relevant record and one labeled irrelevant record."
  ]
}